        "username": "cloudspeech",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/cloudspeech/{size}/330_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-12-04T11:55:06.887Z",
        "cooked": "<p>After some digging around I am pretty sure this is related to <a href=\"https://github.com/apple/foundationdb/issues/274\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">https://github.com/apple/foundationdb/issues/274</a>.</p>\n<p>The issue discussed therein is incompatibility of ZFS with O_DIRECT file I/O, which is<br>\nused by foundationDB.</p>\n<p>The default install of LXD uses ZFS.</p>\n<p>Strace\u2019ing fdbserver uncovers this line involving O_DIRECT:</p>\n<pre><code>openat(AT_FDCWD, \"fdb/4500/processId.part\", \nO_RDWR|O_CREAT|O_TRUNC|O_DIRECT, 02600) = -1 EINVAL (Invalid argument)\n</code></pre>\n<p>Which then leads to:</p>\n<pre><code>write(2, \"ERROR: error creating or opening\"..., 71ERROR: error creating or opening process id file `fdb/4500/processId'.\n) = 71\nwrite(2, \"Fatal Error: Disk i/o operation \"..., 39Fatal Error: Disk i/o operation failed</code></pre>",
        "post_number": 2,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 3,
        "updated_at": "2018-12-04T11:55:06.887Z",
        "reply_count": 1,
        "reply_to_post_number": null,
        "quote_count": 0,
